.TH "pci_hp_add" 9 "pci_hp_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_hp_add \- publish hotplug slot to user space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_hp_add
.BI "(struct hotplug_slot *slot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "slot" 12
pointer to the \fIstruct hotplug_slot\fP to publish
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Make a hotplug slot's sysfs interface available and inform user space of its
addition by sending a uevent.  The hotplug driver must be prepared to handle
all \fIstruct hotplug_slot_ops\fP callbacks from this point on.

Returns 0 on success or a negative int on error.
